defaultA report by the British Medical Journal (BMJ) published in 1994 stated that in inner London, in relation to their traffic volume, HGVs cause 30 times as many cyclists deaths as cars and five times as many as buses.  It 
defaultconcluded: 
default"Until the factors
default leading to this excess risk are understood, a ban on HGVs in urban areas should be considered."
