default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultCurrently most inquest verdicts in the case of road deaths are 
defaultlogged as ‘accidental deaths’, a term families bereaved find insulting. As a result there is no way to count the number of road deaths and therefore acknowledge the true scale of road death and so attached any meaningful priority.
default&#xa0;
defaultRECOMMENDATION:  Introdu
defaultction of a 
defaultspecific short ‘road death’ verdict. 
